      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "CLI: escape zsh completion descriptions",
        "body": "\r\n<img width=\"620\" height=\"177\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/df9f44fb-368a-4de3-abb5-89d714c5cca6\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\n### Problem\r\n\r\nZsh completion descriptions are emitted inside double-quoted `_arguments` specs, but `$` and backticks were not escaped.\r\n\r\nThis means descriptions such as `$OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/completions` or ``models status --json`` can be interpreted by zsh instead of being displayed literally.\r\n\r\n### Why it matters\r\n\r\nThis can break or corrupt CLI tab-completion output and degrades the developer experience.\r\n\r\n### What changed\r\n\r\n- Escaped `$` in zsh completion option descriptions\r\n- Escaped backticks in zsh completion option descriptions\r\n- Added regression tests for both cases\r\n\r\n### What did NOT change\r\n\r\n- No changes to CLI behavior\r\n- No changes to model functionality\r\n- No unrelated changes\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Change Type\r\n\r\n* [x] Bug fix\r\n* [x] Refactor required for the fix\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Scope\r\n\r\n* [x] UI / DX\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\n\r\n* Invalid completion dispatch using `$line[1]` caused `models` to be executed as a command\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## User-visible Changes\r\n\r\n* `openclaw models <TAB>` no longer shows errors\r\n* Subcommands are correctly suggested\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Repro\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nopenclaw models <TAB>\r\n```\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncommand not found: models\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n\r\n```\r\n(subcommands listed)\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Compatibility\r\n\r\n* Backward compatible: Yes\r\n",
